doc.after: Georgian culture evolved over thousands of years with its foundations in Iberian and Colchian civilizations 190 continuing into the rise of the unified Georgian Kingdom under the single monarchy of the Bagrationi Georgian culture enjoyed a golden age and renaissance of classical literature arts philosophy architecture and science in the 11th century 191
